title: So too can the appearance of a lone frequency-1/n (for large n) next to an accented note at a more primary time (frequency 1/k for k larger than n) still constitute presence specifically at that high frequency, even if the more primary time is accented more heavily, particularly if the two are otherwise alone in the nearby 1/n neighborhood
pid: dbcd7b42-955b-4ac7-afc8-8396c10095ac
